INSERT INTO tips (user_id, description)
VALUES (1, 'Vancouver has a relatively mild climate compared to other parts of Canada. The winters are usually not too harsh, and the growing season is extended. Consider planting cold-hardy vegetables like kale, chard, and certain varieties of lettuce that can thrive during the cooler months. Additionally, you can often grow crops well into the fall. Take advantage of the extended growing season to cultivate a wide variety of plants.');

INSERT INTO tips (user_id, description)
VALUES (1, 'Vancouver''s soil may vary, but it often benefits from amendments to improve fertility and drainage. Use organic mulches like compost or well-rotted manure to enrich the soil and help retain moisture. Mulching also helps control weeds. Regularly check and improve the soil structure to ensure optimal conditions for plant growth. Adding organic matter helps with water retention, nutrient availability, and overall soil health.');

INSERT INTO tips (user_id, description)
VALUES (1, 'While Vancouver does receive a fair amount of rainfall, it''s essential to pay attention to watering, especially during drier periods. In the summer, when rainfall may be less consistent, be diligent about watering your garden. However, be mindful not to overwater, as excessive moisture can lead to root diseases. Consider using a drip irrigation system or soaker hoses to provide consistent and efficient watering to your plants.');